893
01:20:30,720 --> 01:20:33,440
If you really simplify it down, 
there are four constraints,  

894
01:20:33,440 --> 01:20:39,120
and each of these can break out into more.
If you switch to DDR, yes, you produce  

895
01:20:39,120 --> 01:20:44,160
four times the bits per DRAM wafer, but all of 
a sudden the constraints shift a lot and your  

896
01:20:44,160 --> 01:20:49,280
