indexing on—is 2048 bits across, connected in an  

902
01:21:16,720 --> 01:21:22,320
area that's 13 millimeters wide.
It transfers memory at around  

903
01:21:22,320 --> 01:21:27,680
10 giga-transfers a second.
So a stack of HBM4 is 2048 bits on  

904
01:21:27,680 --> 01:21:33,840
an area that's roughly 11 to 13 millimeters wide.
That's the shoreline you're taking on the chip. 

905
01:21:33,840 --> 01:21:39,440
In that shoreline, you have 2048 bits 
transferring at 10 giga-transfers per second. 

906
01:21:39,440 --> 01:21:41,280
You multiply those together and divide by eight,  

907
01:21:41,280 --> 01:21:45,680
bits to a byte, and you're at roughly 
