How much more expensive does an iPhone get 
if the memory is two times more expensive? 

936
01:24:09,920 --> 01:24:16,240
I believe an iPhone has 12 gigabytes of memory.
Each gig used to cost roughly $3-4, so that's $50. 

937
01:24:17,280 --> 01:24:23,920
But now the price of memory has tripled.
Let's say it's $12 per gig for DDR. 

938
01:24:23,920 --> 01:24:30,160
Now you're talking about $150 versus $50.
That's a $100 increase in cost for Apple. 

939
01:24:30,160 --> 01:24:32,221
Apple has some margin, they're 
not just going to eat the margin. 

940
01:24:32,221 --> 01:24:32,297
NAND also has the same market dynamics, 
so in reality, it's probably a $150  

941
01:24:32,297 --> 01:24:33,600
increase on the iPhone.
So now that’s a $100 cost  

942
01:24:33,600 --> 01:24:37,440
increase and that’s just on the DRAM.
The NAND also has the same sort of market. 

943
01:24:37,440 --> 01:24:41,440
So in fact it’s probably a 
$150 increase on the iPhone. 

944
01:24:41,440 --> 01:24:46,320
Apple either has to pass that 
on to the consumer or eat it. 

945
01:24:46,320 --> 01:24:49,120
I don't see Apple reducing their margin 
too much, maybe they eat a little bit. 

946
01:24:49,120 --> 01:24:54,000
But at the end of the day, that means the end 
consumer is paying $250 more for an iPhone. 

947
01:24:54,880 --> 01:24:59,120
Now that’s just on last 
year’s pricing versus today’s. 

948
01:24:59,120 --> 01:25:06,480
There is some lag before Apple feels the heat 
because they tend to have long-term contracts  

949
01:25:06,480 --> 01:25:09,920
for memory that last three months to a year.
But at the end of the day, Apple gets hit  

950
01:25:09,920 --> 01:25:13,360
pretty hard by this.
They won't really  

951
01:25:13,360 --> 01:25:17,200
adjust until the next iPhone release.
But that's the high end of the market,  

952
01:25:17,200 --> 01:25:20,640
which is only a few hundred million phones a year.
Apple sells two or three hundred million  

953
01:25:20,640 --> 01:25:25,280
phones annually.
The bulk of the market is mid-range and low-end. 

954
01:25:25,280 --> 01:25:28,320
It used to be that 1.4 billion 
smartphones were sold a year. 

955
01:25:28,320 --> 01:25:31,520
Now we're at about 1.1 billion.
Our projections are that we might  

956
01:25:31,520 --> 01:25:37,200
drop to 800 million this year, and 
down to 500 or 600 million next year. 

957
01:25:37,760 --> 01:25:42,880
We look at data points out of China 
from some of our analysts in Asia,  

958
01:25:42,880 --> 01:25:45,360
Singapore, Hong Kong, and Taiwan.
They've been tracking this,  

959
01:25:45,360 --> 01:25:52,720
