Half the cost of accelerators is memory. 

1009
01:30:09,440 --> 01:30:12,800
Of course they're going to 
start going crazy on it. 

1010
01:30:13,440 --> 01:30:16,480
It took a year for that to 
actually reflect in memory prices. 

1011
01:30:16,480 --> 01:30:20,560
Once memory prices reflected that, it 
took another three to six months for the  

1012
01:30:20,560 --> 01:30:24,240
memory vendors to start building fabs.
Those fabs take two years to build. 

1013
01:30:24,240 --> 01:30:32,240
So we won't have really meaningful fabs to even 
put these tools in until late 2027 or 2028. 

1014
01:30:34,320 --> 01:30:38,800
Instead, you've seen some really 
crazy stuff to get capacity. 

1015
01:30:39,600 --> 01:30:45,440
Micron bought a fab from a company in 
Taiwan that makes lagging-edge chips. 

1016
01:30:47,600 --> 01:30:51,840
Hynix and Samsung are doing some pretty 
crazy things to try and expand capacity  

1017
01:30:51,840 --> 01:30:56,960
