These other tools are also bottlenecks, although 
their supply chains are not as complex as ASML's. 

1024
01:31:30,240 --> 01:31:32,720
You see Applied Materials, Lam 
Research, and all these other  

1025
01:31:32,720 --> 01:31:37,040
companies expanding capacity a lot as well.
But you don't have anywhere to put the tool,  

1026
01:31:37,040 --> 01:31:42,560
because the most complex buildings people make 
are fabs, and fabs take two years to build. 

1027
