For example, energy will not be a big bottleneck  

1039
01:33:40,640 --> 01:33:43,840
a couple of years from now, but that 
doesn't mean energy isn't growing super  

1040
01:33:43,840 --> 01:33:47,120
fast and there's no margin there.
It's just not the key bottleneck. 

1041
01:33:47,120 --> 01:33:52,080
In the space of fabs, clean rooms are the 
biggest bottleneck this year and next year. 

1042
01:33:52,800 --> 01:33:57,520
As we get to 2028, 2029, 2030, there 
will still be constraints there. 

1043
01:33:57,520 --> 01:34:04,080
The thing about Elon is he has a tremendous 
capability to garner physical resources and  

1044
01:34:04,080 --> 01:34:08,560
really smart people to build things.
The way he recruits amazing people  

1045
01:34:08,560 --> 01:34:12,320
is by trying to build the craziest stuff.
In the case of AI, that hasn't really worked  

1046
01:34:12,320 --> 01:34:16,000
because everyone's trying to build AGI. Everyone 
is very ambitious. But in the case of going to  

1047
01:34:17,520 --> 01:34:25,200
Mars, making rockets that land themselves, fully 
autonomous electric cars, or humanoid robots,  

1048
01:34:25,200 --> 01:34:28,800
