I don't think he can develop that quickly. 

1061
01:35:26,880 --> 01:35:32,720
That has a lot of built-up knowledge.
The most complicated integration of  

1062
01:35:32,720 --> 01:35:38,320
very expensive tools and supply chains 
is done by TSMC, Intel, or Samsung. 

1063
01:35:39,040 --> 01:35:43,040
These two other companies aren't even that 
great at it, and they're tremendously complex. 

1064
01:35:43,040 --> 01:35:48,720
How surprised would you be if in 2030 
there just happened to be some total  

1065
01:35:48,720 --> 01:35:52,400
disruption where we're not using EUV?
What if we're using something that has  

1066
01:35:52,400 --> 01:35:56,240
much better effects, is much simpler to produce, 
and can be produced in much bigger quantities? 

1067
01:35:56,240 --> 01:35:58,640
I'm sure as an industry insider that 
sounds like a totally naive question,  

1068
01:35:58,640 --> 01:36:03,760
