There's still a lot of R&D,  

1092
01:38:00,080 --> 01:38:04,400
manufacturing, and integration to be done.
I wouldn't call that out of the cards. 

1093
01:38:04,400 --> 01:38:08,080
I think it's very likely going to happen.
It's also going to require a huge  

1094
01:38:08,080 --> 01:38:11,600
