you’re using EUV in terms of deposition and etch. 

1103
01:38:51,440 --> 01:38:55,040
And the EUV tool has to be there.
Furthermore, when you change to 3D DRAM,  

1104
01:38:55,040 --> 01:38:59,200
there's going to be an even larger shift, so a 
lot of retooling of these fabs needs to happen. 

1105
01:39:01,760 --> 01:39:06,960
That would be a big disruption.
That would make EUV demand generally lower. 

1106
01:39:06,960 --> 01:39:12,240
But as we've seen across time, lithography demand 
as a percentage of wafer cost has trended up. 

1107
01:39:12,240 --> 01:39:24,560
Around the 2014 era, it was 17% of the wafer cost, 
